      • getLocalName

        java.lang.String getLocalName()
        Local names can be used to force several abstract activities within a workflow to be instantiated with one and the same concrete activity (same local name) or different activities (different local names).
        Example:
        Two OCR methods are to be evaluated. The abstract activities for the methods could get local names 'Method_A' and 'Method_B'. The activities for the evaluation, on the other hand, should both get the same local name 'EvaluationMethod' to ensure the same evaluation method is used for both OCR methods.
        Returns:
        The local name of this activity.

      • setLocalName

        void setLocalName(java.lang.String localName)
        Local names can be used to force several abstract activities within a workflow to be instantiated with one and the same concrete activity (same local name) or different activities (different local names).
        Example:

The activities for the evaluation, on the other hand, should both get the same local name 'EvaluationMethod' to ensure the same evaluation method is used for both OCR methods.

      • isAbstract

        boolean isAbstract()
        Returns the abstraction level of this activity (abstract or concrete). A compound activity is abstract if one or more child activities are abstract.
        Returns:
        Returns true if this activity is abstract and false if it is concrete.
